25/05/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Ministers from Albania, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia and Romania met Friday (23 May) to discuss measures to boost tourism in the Balkans.
They decided to set up a ministerial council which would meet once a year to develop common policies in the travel sector.
The ministers adopted a statement highlighting the role of tourism as a factor for development and a means to bring the nations closer to EU membership.
Representatives of the tourism ministers of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia and Turkey also signed the decision.
(AFP - 24/05/03)
